          "output": "Recent updates indicate that new import regulations are set to be implemented in Palestine, effective January 2026. Key points include:\n\n1. **Mandatory Pre-Shipment Inspection**: Certain goods will require inspection certificates prior to shipment.\n2. **Updated HS Code Classification**: There will be adjustments to the classification of imported items.\n3. **Digital Submission of Customs Declarations**: Importers must utilize the ASYCUDA system for submitting customs declarations.\n4. **Increased Inspection Rates**: There will be higher inspection frequency for goods classified as high-risk.\n\nThese changes primarily affect sectors such as food imports, pharmaceuticals, and construction materials. Non-compliance may result in delays, financial penalties (up to 10% of the shipment value), or confiscation of goods.\n\nIt is advised for importers to ensure their documentation is complete, engage certified customs brokers, and stay informed through official Ministry circulars."
        },
